    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Disclosures Regarding Government Reliance in the Space/Launch Segment\n\n## What IS Disclosed\n\n### Government Customer Relationships\nThe preamble identifies the company as **"the primary launch provider for the U.S. government"** and names specific agency customers:\n\n- **NASA** — all five U.S. crew and cargo missions to the ISS in 2025; extended Cargo Resupply Services (CRS) contract driving Launch & Development revenue growth\n- **NRO (National Reconnaissance Office)** — listed among served customers\n- **Department of War** — referenced as a contract revenue driver in both 2024 and 2025\n- **General Services Administration** and **certain Intelligence Community agencies**\n- Commercial customers named: Axiom Space, SES, Eutelsat, Oneweb\n\n### NSSL Program Specifics\n- In 2025, the company launched **11 of 12 NSSL medium and heavy lift missions**\n- U.S. national security customers awarded **~$13.7 billion across NSSL Phase 3 Lane 2 contracts through 2032**, supporting ~54 missions from 2025 to 2032\n- Overall Phase 3 manifest is ~84 missions, nearly double Phase 2\n\n### Contract Structure\nAll launch contracts with U.S. government agencies are **firm fixed-price with milestone-based payments**, subject to FAR and DFARS.\n\n### Qualitative Revenue Drivers\nThe MD&A attributes Launch & Development revenue increases to government contracts (NASA CRS extension, Department of War), but does not quantify the government share.\n\n---\n\n## What IS NOT Disclosed\n\n| Item | Status in Excerpts |\n|---|---|\n| **Percentage of Space segment revenue from government customers** | **Not disclosed** — the revenue table breaks out Launch Services vs. Launch & Development by dollar amount and percentage mix, but never segregates government vs. commercial within either category |\n| **Segment-level customer concentration** (e.g., "Customer X represents Y% of segment revenue") | **Not disclosed** — no single-customer concentration percentage appears anywhere in the provided excerpts |\n| **Government as percentage of total revenue** | **Not disclosed** — while the preamble states "a portion of our revenue is derived from contracts, directly or indirectly, with the U.S. government," no specific percentage is given |\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe filings provide **robust qualitative disclosure** about the company\'s deep entanglement with U.S. government space programs — naming NASA, NRO, the Department of War, and quantifying the $13.7 billion NSSL Phase 3 award — but they **do not quantify** what share of Space segment (or total) revenue originates from government customers, nor do they provide segment-level customer concentration figures. An investor can infer significant government dependence from the narrative (primary government launch provider, 11/12 NSSL missions, all NASA crewed flights, government contracts driving Launch & Development growth), but the excerpts stop short of stating an explicit percentage.',
